    modified_response: "I have built the **Vibe Coder Parody WebApp**, dedicated purely to mocking chaotic vibe coding practices. \n\nHere is what was intentionally engineered to be as \"shitty\" and funny as requested:\n\n- **The \"High Security\" OTP Meme**: Implemented a mock phone number signup where clicking \"SEND ME THE SECURE OTP\" simply console logs the passcode and drops a giant green banner in the UI physically showing the code because \"I didn\'t setup Twilio yet bro.\"\n- **Flawless State Management Counter**: An increment counter that randomly uses string concatenation (`+ \"1\"`), sets the state to `NaN`, or randomly decrements the value to mock AI hallucinating random React state architectures without understanding types (`TS: any`).\n- **Chaotic Layout & Visuals**:\n  - The styling defaults to the infamous `Comic Sans MS`.\n  - Intentionally clashing `cyan-300`, `fuchsia-300`, and hyper-neon colors. \n  - Fake rotating `LGTM! \360\237\221\215` and constant vibrating UI elements that cause anxiety.\n  - A bottom `marquee` bar constantly warning the visitors about an `Unhandled Promise Rejection`.\n- **Marquee \"Debugging\" Logs**: An old-school scrolling window in the hero mimicking typical AI developer spam outputs (`console.log(\"here\"); console.log(\"here 2\");`).\n\nEverything is connected to function as an interactive joke. Let me know if you want to add any other specific classic developer or vibe coding internet memes!"
