  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Initiating the Analysis**\n\nI\'m diving into this request to enhance the \"vibe coding\" parody site. My focus is on gathering relatable satire: humorous bugs, questionable design decisions, and those developer struggles that hit home. The OTP-instead-of-the-actual-code gag is a great example of the tone I\'m aiming for. I\'m building a repository of these elements.\n\n\n**Expanding the Satire**\n\nI\'m now focusing on specific meme-worthy components. I\'m working on the \"impossible div centering\" component, planning the code for the AI overuse comment component, and sketching out an \"it works on my machine\" badge. I will look for ways to bring these elements to life.\n\n\n**Developing the Details**\n\nI\'ve hit a wave of fresh meme ideas. There are spinners that serve no purpose, a blinding light/dark mode switch that I envision as a CSS-breaking disaster, and the horrifying unnecessary npm package that is \"is-even\". I am now also going to write about the phone number form that is a dropdown slider, and the dreaded \"any\" type in TypeScript. My goal is to add these concepts to the project\'s codebase.\n\n\n\n**Implementing the Features**\n\nI\'m now writing the awful code. I\'ve started adding the new terrible UI components, including the phone number slider (it goes to eleven!), a ridiculously centered div, and the \"AI-generated dark mode\" toggle that\'s just a garish CSS filter. I\'m also refining the OTP signup for extra absurdity.\n\n\n**Crafting the Implementation**\n\nI\'m now generating actual code. I\'ve got a truly awful phone number input using a slider, and I\'m adding an \"architecture diagram\" component, which contains absurd, AI-generated code comments. I am going to put these micro-memes in the project now. My goal is to build a `MemeGallery` or similar for this.\n\n\n**Adding the Micro-Meme Components**\n\nI\'m now generating specific terrible UI components as React files. I\'m adding `TerriblePhoneInput.tsx` and the mocked `IsEven.tsx`, then updating `App.tsx` to include them. I\'m also adding a terrible CSS filter for the dark mode, and will add the \"It works on my machine\" badge to the project. I\'ll test these out as I add them.\n\n\n**Adding the Running Button**\n\nI\'ve just added the fleeing button \342\200\223 it\'s a \"Submit PR\" button that scurries away from the cursor, embodying a developer\'s fear. I\'m building out `src/components/TerribleUI.tsx` to collect these elements. I\'m also planning to implement the \"Dependencies: 14,000\" gag in the tech stack and the !important on everything as well.\n\n\n**Adding the Phone Slider**\n\nI\'m now integrating the phone number slider component, which I built with React, and I\'m adding it to the project. I\'m focusing on the slider\'s absurd precision, which allows the user to meticulously select each digit of their phone number. I\'m also ensuring the UX of the component is terrible.\n\n\n\n**Refining the UI**\n\nI\'m now focusing on refining the \"Approve Pull Request\" button, making it even more frustrating to interact with. I\'m also working on the \"AI-generated dark mode\" toggle. I am enhancing its functionality so it\'s as disruptive as possible, reflecting the original concept. I\'m integrating these components into `src/components/TerribleUI.tsx`.\n\n\n**Enhancing the Dark Mode**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the \'AI-generated dark mode\' toggle. The new implementation features a jarring, inverting filter with a rotating animation on the button to highlight its disruptive nature. I\'m also planning to create a \'CodeSnippet\' component with terrible AI-generated code and ridiculous comments. I think this will capture the tone I am going for!\n\n\n**Generating the AI Snippet**\n\nI\'m now integrating an AI-generated code snippet component. I\'m focusing on the \"Copilot Hall of Fame,\" complete with absurd comments and an intentionally incorrect, generic function (the `isEven` function) to demonstrate AI\'s potential for generating confusing code. I\'ll test it out as I add it.\n\n\n**Refining the \"Is Even\" Function**\n\nI\'m now iterating on the `isEven` function, adding to the absurdity. I have introduced an intentionally incomplete pattern, where the \"if\" statements cover only a small fraction of the possibilities, and inserted an extremely large number of \"hidden\" lines to simulate an incorrect implementation. My plan is to add more non-sensical, and possibly harmful, code.\n\n\n**Integrating the Hall of Fame**\n\nI\'m now integrating the updated AI-generated code snippet into the project, including the \"Copilot Hall of Fame.\" I will also make updates to `App.tsx` and the general layout to include these new components. I am planning to add the \"Works on my machine\" badge to `Hero.tsx`, using an absolute positioned stamp and rotation. Finally, I will add a StackOverflow button to highlight the project\'s development.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 67
      nanos: 704363513
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
