  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Refactoring Usability**\n\nI\'ve successfully refactored the application. It now boasts a cohesive and usable workflow, transforming it into a real-world SaaS application, akin to \"VibeTask,\" with a functioning login flow. Users are immediately greeted by the landing page, and I will be working from there.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have completely refactored the application into a cohesive, interactive system. It now functions as a \"usable\" task management app called **VibeTask\342\204\242 Pro**, built entirely around the worst and funniest \"vibe coding\" practices, while maintaining an actual logical workflow.\n\nHere is what was successfully implemented:\n\n- **The Bank-Grade Auth Workflow**: I modified the signup component so it actively guards the application. The user is now forced to use the terrible 1 to 9,999,999,999 **phone number slider** to enter their number, generate the OTP, and then \"whisper\" it to log in.\n- **The Spaghetti Loading Screen**: A chaotic loading component with multiple overlapping layers, colliding css spins, and a fake `npm install` terminal feed that simulates a massive system leak while transitioning to the dashboard.\n- **VibeTask\342\204\242 Pro Dashboard**: Once logged in, the user gets access to the usable core app, filled with terrible UX decisions:\n  - **The Fleeing Button**: The \"ADD IT\" button for a new task will run away from the user\'s cursor the first three times they try to click it.\n  - **AI Intent Matching (Bugs)**: Checking a task to mark it \"done\" has a 25% chance to mark a different, random task entirely, claiming that \"Copilot predicted you actually meant to complete a different task\".\n  - **Fake Promise Rejections**: Deleting a task has a chance to throw a fake system-level connection drop alert, followed immediately by just forcibly hiding the DOM element away so it \"looks\" deleted.\n- **Persistent AI Elements**: The \"Hall of Fame\" and the hilarious AI pair programming chat logs are now structured as the active documentation pane inside your authenticated tech dashboard. \n\nThe application is completely usable end-to-end, serving as a fully functional, yet endlessly frustrating parody of the vibe coding movement!"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 2
      nanos: 209595963
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
